<task id="UDSS-017" project="UI Dialog Shell Standardization">
  <metadata>
    <title>Complete Corporate Workspace restructuring — remove all inline dialogs</title>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <phase>2</phase>
    <estimated-effort>6 hours</estimated-effort>
    <tags>workspace, restructuring, navigateTo, code-cleanup</tags>
    <dependencies>011c, 012c, 013c, 014c, 015c</dependencies>
    <parallel-group>none</parallel-group>
  </metadata>
  <prompt>Remove ALL remaining inline dialog components from WorkspaceGrid.tsx (or equivalent Corporate Workspace main file) and replace them with navigateTo webresource calls to the new Code Pages. This task completes the Corporate Workspace restructuring started in Phase 1 (task 009). After this task, WorkspaceGrid.tsx should be under 500 LOC with zero lazy-imported wizard/dialog components.</prompt>
  <role>Frontend developer with expertise in React 19, Fluent UI v9, and Dataverse Code Pages</role>
  <goal>WorkspaceGrid.tsx under 500 LOC, zero inline wizard/dialog imports, all 5 wizards launched via navigateTo, post-dialog refresh working for all</goal>
  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-012">Services must use IDataService abstraction, no direct webApi</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-006">Code Pages are default UI surface — PCF only for form-bound controls</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-021">Fluent v9 tokens only, React 19, dark mode required</constraint>
    <constraint source="architecture">navigateTo Promise must trigger data refresh after dialog close</constraint>
    <constraint source="quality">WorkspaceGrid.tsx must be under 500 LOC after cleanup</constraint>
  </constraints>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-006-anti-legacy-js.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-012-shared-components.md</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/pcf/dialog-patterns.md</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/webresource/custom-dialogs-in-dataverse.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <steps>
    <step id="1">Identify all remaining lazy imports of wizard/dialog components in WorkspaceGrid.tsx (CreateEvent, CreateTodo, CreateWorkAssignment, SummarizeFiles, FindSimilar)</step>
    <step id="2">Remove all 5 lazy import statements and their associated React.Suspense wrappers</step>
    <step id="3">Remove all associated state hooks (isCreateEventOpen, isCreateTodoOpen, etc.) and their setter calls</step>
    <step id="4">Replace each dialog trigger with a navigateTo call to the corresponding Code Page webresource (sprk_createeventwizard, sprk_createtodowizard, sprk_createworkassignmentwizard, sprk_summarizefileswizard, sprk_findsimilar)</step>
    <step id="5">Wire navigateTo Promise .then() to trigger data refresh after each dialog closes (refetch workspace data)</step>
    <step id="6">Configure navigateTo options: target=2, width=85%, height=85% for wizards; appropriate sizing for FindSimilar dialog</step>
    <step id="7">Pass required data params via navigateTo data string (entityId, entityType, containerId, etc.)</step>
    <step id="8">Remove any now-unused imports, types, and utility functions related to inline dialogs</step>
    <step id="9">Verify WorkspaceGrid.tsx is under 500 LOC</step>
    <step id="10">Run tsc to verify compilation</step>
    <step id="11">Build the Corporate Workspace solution (npm run build in src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/) to verify no build errors</step>
  </steps>
  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>WorkspaceGrid.tsx is under 500 LOC</criterion>
    <criterion>Zero lazy-imported wizard/dialog components remain</criterion>
    <criterion>Zero dialog state hooks (isXxxOpen) remain for removed wizards</criterion>
    <criterion>All 5 wizards launch via Xrm.Navigation.navigateTo with correct webresource names</criterion>
    <criterion>Post-dialog data refresh works for all 5 navigateTo calls</criterion>
    <criterion>navigateTo uses appropriate modal sizing (85% x 85% for wizards)</criterion>
    <criterion>Data params (entityId, entityType, etc.) passed correctly to each Code Page</criterion>
    <criterion>tsc compiles without errors</criterion>
    <criterion>Corporate Workspace solution builds successfully</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
